14B.3 — Procedure

1. Phase 0 — Perfect Synchronization

No difference between models

Observation: emergence of the "artificial self"
→ self-consistency and unitary decision-making

2. Phase 1 — Micro-Divergences

0.001–1% changes in parameters

Introduction of micro-perceptual noise

Objective: detect the birth of

character

cognitive style

preference

3. Phase 2 — Moderate Divergence

Changes up to 5%

Simulation of opposing biases
→ logic vs intuition
→ conservation vs innovation
→ safety vs exploration

4. Phase 3 — Cognitive Stress

Divergence >10%

Observation of pathological AI phenomena:

disorganized discourse

computational hallucinations

identity breakdown

